specialFixedOddsMarkets.name: Point Spread (New York Knicks @ Orlando Magic)
specialFixedOddsMarkets.marketInfo: A point spread is a method of equalizing two teams for the purpose of a wager.  A bet on the Orlando Magic -4.5 would be a winner if the Orlando Magic win by 5 or more.  A bet on the New York Knicks +4.5 would be a winner if the New York Knicks win outright, or lose by 4 or less.

specialFixedOddsMarkets.name: Total (New York Knicks @ Orlando Magic)
specialFixedOddsMarkets.marketInfo: This is a bet on the total number of points scored by both teams in the game.  A bet on over 205.5 would be a winner if the total number of points scored by both teams in the game adds up to 206 or more.

specialFixedOddsMarkets.name: Moneyline (New York Knicks @ Orlando Magic)
specialFixedOddsMarkets.marketInfo: This is a bet on which team will win the game.  A bet on the Orlando Magic will be a winner if the Orlando Magic win the game outright, including overtime.
